[test pragmatics]
# gen338 — L13 PRAGMATICA (abstraction-ceiling beyond L12): reading between
# the lines as KB knowledge. The act types are a KB registry (pragma_act/1 in
# kb/core/pragmatics.p0, included by social.p0); surface forms are intent_cue
# facts, replies response_template facts, and «what does … usually/really
# mean?» is served by the generic answer_frame engine over pragmatic_meaning/2
# — a new act or idiom is facts, zero C. Pulled from real walls (gen338 probe
# battery): the salt request was deflected as smalltalk, the cold hint walled,
# the quoted-pronoun question was hijacked by coref repair.
> can you pass me the salt?
< I read that as a request, not a question about ability -- but I have no hands. Anything I can do with words?
> it is cold in here
< Said like that, it's usually a hint -- close the window, adjust the heat. I can't reach either, but I take the point.
> what does "nice weather, isn't it" usually mean?
< Commenting on the weather is usually small talk -- an invitation to chat, not a report.
> what does "the elephant in the room" really mean?
< The elephant in the room is the obvious problem everyone avoids naming.
> puoi aprire la finestra?
< La leggo come una richiesta, non una domanda sulle mie capacita -- ma non ho mani. Posso aiutarti a parole?
> fa freddo qui
< Detta cosi, di solito e un'allusione -- chiudi la finestra, alza il calore. Non posso farlo, ma colgo il punto.
